Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_offchip_package_trace(25.10)              set_offchip_package_trace(25.10)

Name
       set_offchip_package_trace - Specifies to include RDL0 (off-chip package
       trace) resistance effects during the static and dynamic rail analysis

Syntax
       set_offchip_package_trace

       [-help]

       -mapping <mapping_file>

       -name <switched_name>

       -ploc_file_list <list_of_bump_location_files>

       [-reset]

       -spice <spice_model_name>

       [-subckt <subcircuitname>]

       Specifies  to  include RDL0 (off-chip package trace) resistance effects
       during the static and dynamic rail analysis. This flow  allows  you  to
       analyze  switched  net  bumps  that are marked as RDL0 bumps. When this
       command is specified, the software automatically generates switched net
       bump   current   and   bump   voltage    waveforms    in    the    vol-
       tus_rail_pad.tran.ptiavg  file  created in the new switch net directory
       located under the rail state directory.

       You can specify multiple set_offchip_package_trace commands  to  define
       connectivity of different bump nets.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each set_offchip_package_trace parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command man set_offchip_package_trace.

       -mapping <mapping_file>
              Specifies the name of the mapping file that contains the mapping
              between the package port and switched net bump names. The format
              of the file is:

              <spice_circuit_port_name> pin <vsrcName_in_switch_net's_ploc>

       -name <trace_model_name>
              Specifies the trace model name or switched net bump of RDL0.

       -ploc_file_list <list_of_bump_location_files>
              Specifies the name of a file containing switched net  names  and
              associated ploc/power pad files. The format of the file is:

              SWITCHED_NET1 plocfile1

              SWITCHED_NET2 plocfile2

              .....

              The format of plocfile (power pad) is:

              <voltage_source_name> <x> <y> <metal_layer>

              The   format   of  this  file  is  same  as  specified  for  the
              set_power_pads -format xy format.

       -reset Resets all the previous set_offchip_package_trace  command  set-
              tings to the default settings.

       -spice<model_file>
              Specifies  a file containing a SPICE subcircuit (RDL0 netlist or
              full-chip package netlist) for off-chip package trace.

       -subckt <subcircuitname>
              Defines the top-level subcircuit for off-chip package tracing.

Examples
              * The following command specifies to analyze  the  switched  net
                VDDau:

                set_offchip_package_trace    -name    VDDau    -ploc_file_list
                ploc_file_list.txt -spice pkg.ckt -mapping pkg_mapping.file

